This executive order, issued by President Trump on August 15, 2017, aims to improve the federal environmental review and permitting process for infrastructure projects. The purpose of the order is to increase infrastructure investment in the US, strengthen the economy, create jobs, and reduce the costs of goods and services. The order establishes policies to ensure informed decision-making, environmental sensitivity, transparency, accountability, and efficient processes. It sets a goal of completing all federal environmental reviews and authorization decisions for major infrastructure projects within 2 years. The order also includes definitions of key terms, provisions for agency performance accountability, process enhancements, and the revocation of a previous executive order on flood risk management.